Company: California Department of Justice, Computer and Technology Crime High-Tech Response Team (CATCH)
Description of incident: In November 2011, hackers accessed and released private email accounts belonging to a retired agent for the Department of Justice.  The retired agent was a member of the CATCH.  Some of the emails that the hackers released included data that contained the names, Social Security numbers, addresses, dates of birth, and other personal information of an unknown number of consumers.
